openblocks.workspace.typeblocking
Class TypeBlockManager

java.lang.Object
  openblocks.workspace.typeblocking.TypeBlockManager

public class TypeBlockManager
extends Object

The TypeBlockManager primary serves to help users drop blocks manually into the bock canvas through the keyboard. To achieve this, the TypeBlockManager commands three distinct phases: Interfacing, Searching, Dropping.

enableTypeBlockManager

public static TypeBlockManager enableTypeBlockManager(BlockCanvas component)
Enables singleton instance of TypeBLockManager. If manager is enabled, computation is done over user-generated input.

disableTypeBlockManager

public static void disableTypeBlockManager()
Disables the TypeBlockManager. When disabled, TypeBlockManager still consumes key inputs but never proceeds to Phase 2. That is, the user-generated pattern is never parsed.

automateBlockInsertion

protected static void automateBlockInsertion(String genusName,
                                             String label)
Parameters:
genusName -
label -
Effects:
Do nothing if "genusName" does not map to a valid block. Otherwise, create and add a new block with matching genus and label properties to one of the following: 1. the current block with focus at (0,0) relative to that block. 2. the current block with focus at next applicable socket location 3. the canvas at the last mouse click point. Then update any focus and block connections.
Modifies:
focusManager.focusblock && focusManager.focuspoint && blockCanvas
Requires:
if (label != null) then associated block.isLabelEditable() should return true

automateBlockInsertion

protected static void automateBlockInsertion(TextualFactoryBlock block,
                                             String label)
Effects:
Do nothing if "genusName" does not map to a valid block. Otherwise, create and add a new block with matching genus and label properties to one of the following: 1. the current block with focus at (0,0) relative to that block. 2. the current block with focus at next applicable socket location 3. the canvas at the last mouse click point. If label is not an empty string, then set the block label to that string. Then update any focus and block connections.
Modifies:
focusManager.focusblock && focusManager.focuspoint && blockCanvas
Requires:
none
